  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 160°C/ 140°C (fan)/ gas 3</p><p>Rinse the<strong> puy-style lentils</strong> in a sieve under <strong>cold running water</strong></p><p>Then, add the <strong>puy-style lentils</strong> to a pot with plenty of<strong> cold water</strong>, bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 20-25 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain and rinse under <strong>cold water</strong> until cooled slightly</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1728.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1728.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1728.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1728.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1728.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the lentils are cooking, chop the<strong> heritage tomatoes</strong> and<strong> cherry tomatoes</strong> in half</p><p>Add the <strong>halved tomatoes</strong> to a baking tray with a generous drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 20-25 min or until softened – these are your <strong>slow-roasted tomatoes</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1728.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1728.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1728.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1728.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1728.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, crumble the <strong>feta</strong> onto one side of a separate baking tray and add the<strong> pine nut & seed mix </strong>(leave some space on the tray for later!)</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for an initial 15 min or until golden and crisp</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1728.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1728.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1728.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1728.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1728.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the feta and pine nuts & seeds are baking, peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>In a large bowl, combine the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> (don't like raw garlic? Go easy!) with the <strong>Dijon mustard</strong>, <strong>balsamic vinegar</strong>, 3 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [6 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong>, 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> and a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>– this is your <strong>balsamic vinaigrette</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1728.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
